So I decided that I need to learn to crochet. I know I have some artsy friends here...so if you crochet, please recommend some books to me! Please!

Also, I bought this birdie kit to make this birdie today and I am determined to give Ron my finished product. Haha. Poor Ron...it'll probably still look like a ball of yarn...only in knots. >.< Oyy.

I totally recommend that seller on Etsy by the way! She was sooo sweet! She threw in a finished birdie so that I can have it as a guide! Yay! All this for $12.50 Bird + supplies for bird #2. I'm happy. I made a good purchase. ^_^

 I'm off to the library today at 6:00pm EST sooo if you have any book recommendations, please make them in the next two hours! If not, I'll check them out in like 2 weeks.

Thanks!

Ok. I think Holly has helped most of us in one way or another. I mean, just by the m_girlfriends group she was a HUGE help for all the lonely mish gfs.

I'm no longer a mish gf as you all know...but I still stick around because I love all the girls there! =)

Here's my plan. I want to give Holly and Dominic a great gift. Something amazing...from all of us! I'd make the card and buy the gift since she sent me an invite.

I can take donations through PayPal if you guys/girls are interested. You don't have to have a PayPal account to make a donation. A credit card or Debit/ATM card is fine. This will only be up for a day, since I really don't want Holly to find out. So please spread the word and block Holly out of this, ok? =)

 




This button will also be on m_girlfriends.

*~*Marlene*~*

I'm starting to sell jewelry handmade by my friend! I've placed a few pictures. If you live in Miami, message me and we can arrange a meeting so you can look at some of the jewelry. Prices are typically $7/each or $21 for an earring, bracelet, necklace set. She can subsitute or add an anklet if you would like to include it in a set. Prices are subject to change, but we will give you a notice.




She made this to match the pink & red earring/bracelt set she gave me for my birthday. 





She made this one for Ron's mom. 





This one is for sale.




Some of the older work.




More of her older work.



If you are in Utah, comment and I will have Line (the one that makes the jewelry) contact you.

If you live in any other state, please comment and I or Line will arrange the shipping.

Now, all I need to know is...will you guys (for your girlfriends or wives) or girls, be interested in buying stuff like this? She can make them to your liking. These are only a few pictures that I managed to snag. ^_^

You can also email both of us at: iBeads.Management@Gmail.com or check out our new community: iBeads_Jewelry

Thanks!

*~*Marlene*~*

Teen Commandments:
  1. Don't let your parents down; they brought you up.
  2. Choose your companions with care; you become what they are.
  3. Be master of your habits or they will master you.
  4. Treasure your time; don't spend it, invest it.
  5. Stand for something or you'll fall for anything.
  6. Select only a date that would make a good mate.
  7. See what you can do for others; not what they can do for you.
  8. Guard your thoughts, what you think, what you are.
  9. Don't fill up on this world's crumbs; feed your soul on living bread.
  10. Give your all to Christ; He gave His all for you.

Welcome

This is 's livejournal. Welcome to my insanity. In this journal you will see your fair share of quizzes, days at school, days with friends, and other pure craziness.

ENTER AT YOUR OWN RISK.

Leave comments here including what you think about me, what you think about my layout, and any other randomness that you can think of.
Have a nice day! ^_~

~*~Friends/Invite Only~*~


My journal is friends only for several reasons. Primary being that I like to know who is reading my journal. I sometimes write nonesense and sometimes I write from deep in my heart. It's all me though and I like to be aware of who has access.

If you would like to be added then please leave a comment. If you were on my friends list and now find you arent - dont take it personally - you were either removed because we just dont click or havent updated your journal in a month or more. Or we had conflict. Sorry.

I dont add everyone that comments. Again, dont take it personally but if I feel we dont really share any common interests or if you are a hater then I won't add you. Sorry.

Comments will be deleted after I have read and/or responded to them.
